{"parse":{"title":"Equality of autonomy","pageid":32453192,"revid":791496919,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Equality of autonomy</b> is a <a href=\"/wiki/Political_philosophy\" title=\"Political philosophy\">political philosophy</a> concept of <a href=\"/wiki/Amartya_Sen\" title=\"Amartya Sen\">Amartya Sen</a> that argues \"that the ability and means to choose our life course should be spread as equally as possible across society\"\u2014i.e., an equal chance at <a href=\"/wiki/Autonomy\" title=\"Autonomy\">autonomy</a> or <a href=\"/wiki/Empowerment\" title=\"Empowerment\">empowerment</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-twsO23_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-twsO23-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> Equality of autonomy strives to spread empowerment widely so that \"given their circumstances\", people have more \"choice and control\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-twsO24_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-twsO24-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> The concept has a slightly different emphasis from related notions, such as the value of <a href=\"/wiki/Inequality_in_the_workplace\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Inequality in the workplace\">equality in the workplace</a> (\"<a href=\"/wiki/Equal_opportunity\" title=\"Equal opportunity\">equal opportunity</a>\") or equal material wealth (\"<a href=\"/wiki/Equality_of_outcome\" title=\"Equality of outcome\">equality of outcome</a>\").\n</p><p>According to <a href=\"/wiki/Todd_May\" title=\"Todd May\">Todd May</a>, Sen's approach requires \"<a href=\"/wiki/Economic_interventionism\" title=\"Economic interventionism\">active intervention</a> of institutions like the state into people's lives\" but with an aim towards \"fostering of people's self-creation rather than their living conditions\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-twsO25_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-twsO25-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> Sen argued that \"the ability to convert incomes into opportunities is affected by a multiplicity of individual and social differences that mean some people will need more than others to achieve the same range of <a href=\"/wiki/Capability_approach\" title=\"Capability approach\">capabilities</a>\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-twsO45_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-twsO45-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Equality_of_autonomy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Capability_approach\" title=\"Capability approach\">Capability approach</a></li>\n<li><i><a href=\"/wiki/Development_as_Freedom\" title=\"Development as Freedom\">Development as Freedom</a></i></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Egalitarianism\" title=\"Egalitarianism\">Egalitarianism</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Equality_of_opportunity\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Equality of opportunity\">Equality of opportunity</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Equality_of_outcome\" title=\"Equality of outcome\">Equality of outcome</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Inequity_aversion\" title=\"Inequity aversion\">Inequity aversion</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Equality_of_autonomy&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-twsO23-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-twsO23_1-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Sunder Katwala (21 October 2010). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2010/oct/21/equality-life-chances-not-literal-left\">\"It's equality of life chances, not literal equality, that the left espouses\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Guardian\" title=\"The Guardian\">The Guardian</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2011-07-15</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=The+Guardian&amp;rft.atitle=It%27s+equality+of+life+chances%2C+not+literal+equality%2C+that+the+left+espouses&amp;rft.date=2010-10-21&amp;rft.au=Sunder+Katwala&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fcommentisfree%2F2010%2Foct%2F21%2Fequality-life-chances-not-literal-left&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEquality+of+autonomy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-twsO24-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-twsO24_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20120307214013/http://www.hullpct.nhs.uk/impact_assessments/\">\"Equality Impact Assessments\"</a>. <i>Hull Teaching Primary Care</i>. 2011-07-15. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.hullpct.nhs.uk/impact_assessments/\">the original</a> on 2012-03-07<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2011-07-15</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Equality+Impact+Assessments&amp;rft.date=2011-07-15&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.hullpct.nhs.uk%2Fimpact_assessments%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEquality+of+autonomy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-twsO25-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-twsO25_3-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation book\"><a href=\"/wiki/Todd_May\" title=\"Todd May\">Todd May</a> (2008). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=JJYjY8sG85kC&amp;pg=PA19&amp;lpg=PA19&amp;dq=%22equality+of+autonomy%22&amp;source=bl&amp;ots=zHHGkwrGBm&amp;sig=J6qBAQ5E5UjlZZz4Usv0UQ_5ElI&amp;hl=en&amp;ei=ZpAjTrjdCpO40AH_g8ilAw&amp;sa=X&amp;oi=book_result&amp;ct=result&amp;resnum=3&amp;ved=0CCYQ6AEwAg#v=onepage&amp;q=%22equality%20of%20autonomy%22&amp;f=false\"><i>The Political Thought of Jacques Ranci\u00e8re: Creating Equality</i></a>. The Pennsylvania State University Press. p.&#160;20<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2011-07-15</span></span>. <q>Amartya Sen has developed a theory of <a href=\"/wiki/Distributive_justice\" title=\"Distributive justice\">distributive justice</a> that, like <a href=\"/wiki/John_Rawls\" title=\"John Rawls\">Rawls</a>', requires the active intervention of institutions like the state into people's lives, but like <a href=\"/wiki/Robert_Nozick\" title=\"Robert Nozick\">Nozick</a>'s, aims that intervention at the fostering of people's self-creation rather than their living conditions. For Sen, the proper focus of a theory of justice is on what he calls <i>capabilities</i>, and he defines those capabilities on the basis of what he calls <i>functionings</i>.</q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=The+Political+Thought+of+Jacques+Ranci%C3%A8re%3A+Creating+Equality&amp;rft.pages=20&amp;rft.pub=The+Pennsylvania+State+University+Press&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft.au=Todd+May&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.com%2Fbooks%3Fid%3DJJYjY8sG85kC%26pg%3DPA19%26lpg%3DPA19%26dq%3D%2522equality%2Bof%2Bautonomy%2522%26source%3Dbl%26ots%3DzHHGkwrGBm%26sig%3DJ6qBAQ5E5UjlZZz4Usv0UQ_5ElI%26hl%3Den%26ei%3DZpAjTrjdCpO40AH_g8ilAw%26sa%3DX%26oi%3Dbook_result%26ct%3Dresult%26resnum%3D3%26ved%3D0CCYQ6AEwAg%23v%3Donepage%26q%3D%2522equality%2520of%2520autonomy%2522%26f%3Dfalse&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEquality+of+autonomy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-twsO45-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-twsO45_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">Anne Phillips (2004). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://eprints.lse.ac.uk/533/\">\"Defending Equality of Outcome\"</a>. <i>Journal of Political Philosophy</i>: 1\u201319<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2011-07-15</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Journal+of+Political+Philosophy&amp;rft.atitle=Defending+Equality+of+Outcome&amp;rft.pages=1-19&amp;rft.date=2004&amp;rft.au=Anne+Phillips&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Feprints.lse.ac.uk%2F533%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AEquality+of+autonomy\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Sanzio_01_Plato_Aristotle.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Sanzio_01_Plato_Aristotle.jpg/23px-Sanzio_01_Plato_Aristotle.jpg\" width=\"23\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Sanzio_01_Plato_Aristotle.jpg/34px-Sanzio_01_Plato_Aristotle.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/98/Sanzio_01_Plato_Aristotle.jpg/46px-Sanzio_01_Plato_Aristotle.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"804\" data-file-height=\"1052\" /></a></td><td><i>This article about <a href=\"/wiki/Politi